.TH "sched_setscheduler" 9 "sched_setscheduler" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sched_setscheduler \- change the scheduling policy and/or RT priority of a thread.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sched_setscheduler
.BI "(struct task_struct *p "  ","
.BI "int policy "  ","
.BI "const struct sched_param *param "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
the task in question.
.IP "policy" 12
new policy.
.IP "param" 12
structure containing the new RT priority.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Use \fBsched_set_fifo\fP, read its comment.

NOTE that the task may be already dead.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success. An error code otherwise.
